### 7. Client vs Supplier Journey Banner — Transition Hub

```
At the top of an existing Transition Intelligence Hub 
page, above the main stats row (Total Scope 3 Exposure, 
High-Risk Suppliers etc.), add a horizontal 
two-lane journey banner.

The banner is a full-width card with light gray 
background, divided into two lanes by a 
vertical divider line in the center:

LEFT LANE — labeled "Corporate Client Journey" 
with a small building icon:
Show 4 steps as pills connected by arrows:
[Assess Data] → [Map Supply Chain] → 
[Prioritise Risks] → [Notify Suppliers ✓]
The last step "Notify Suppliers" is filled red 
(active/complete). Others are outlined gray. 
Small label below: "StyleSphere Apparel — 
your journey ends here"

RIGHT LANE — labeled "Supplier Journey" 
with a factory icon:
Show 4 steps as pills connected by arrows:
[Receive Invite] → [ESG Assessment] → 
[Access Roadmap] → [Begin Transition]
All steps outlined in green, not yet active.
Small label below: "Suppliers own their 
transition — HSBC connects both sides"

CENTER DIVIDER: Small HSBC hexagon logo 
or red circle with "HSBC" at the intersection 
point between the two lanes, visually 
showing HSBC as the connector.

Banner height: ~80px. Subtle drop shadow. 
Collapsible with a small chevron on the right.
```

---

These prompts are self-contained — you can paste each one directly into Claude, v0, or any design tool to generate the component. Start with **prompt 7** (the journey banner) and **prompt 1** (revenue opportunities) as they'll have the biggest impact on your judges.
